# Podman/Docker honor this, not .gitignore. Keep host build/editor state out of
# the build context so `COPY . .` never drags a locally-compiled .scala-build
# (a possibly different scala-cli/JDK) into the in-container compile — CI checks
# out clean, but the documented `podman build … scala` runs from a working tree.
.scala-build/
.bsp/
.metals/
.bloop/
target/
*.jar
